```
Text-based Circuit Diagram (ESP32 WROOM-32 + L298N + Soil Sensor)

Power Connections:
------------------
(External 12V Power Supply)
   +12V  ------------------>  L298N 12V (VMS)
   GND   ------------------>  L298N GND
                            |
                            +-->  ESP32 GND (Common Ground)
                            +-->  Soil Sensor GND

ESP32 Power:
   ESP32 5V (from USB or Regulated 5V) ----------------> Board Power
   ESP32 3.3V ----------------------------------------> Soil Sensor VCC


Motor Driver (L298N Module):
----------------------------
[Left Motor: Pump 1]
   Motor A Terminal 1  <---->  L298N OUT1
   Motor A Terminal 2  <---->  L298N OUT2

[Right Motor: Pump 2]
   Motor B Terminal 1  <---->  L298N OUT3
   Motor B Terminal 2  <---->  L298N OUT4

[Control Pins - ESP32 to L298N]
   ESP32 GPIO 26  ------------------>  L298N IN1
   ESP32 GPIO 25  ------------------>  L298N IN2
   ESP32 GPIO 14  ------------------>  L298N ENA (PWM for Pump 1)

   ESP32 GPIO 27  ------------------>  L298N IN3
   ESP32 GPIO 33  ------------------>  L298N IN4
   ESP32 GPIO 12  ------------------>  L298N ENB (PWM for Pump 2)

   (Jumper on ENA & ENB placed to enable both channels)


Soil Moisture Sensor:
---------------------
   Soil Sensor VCC  ------------------>  ESP32 3.3V
   Soil Sensor GND  ------------------>  ESP32 GND
   Soil Sensor Analog Output --------->  ESP32 GPIO 32 (SOIL_PIN)


Summary:
--------
- ESP32 controls two pumps using L298N through IN1–IN4 and PWM pins ENA, ENB.
- Soil moisture sensor connected to GPIO 32 for analog readings.
- All grounds are common between ESP32, L298N, and power supply.
- Jumper on L298N enables internal 5V regulator for logic supply (if module provides it).
- Ensure ESP32 is not powered from L298N’s 5V regulator; use USB or separate 5V regulated source.
```
